3. Set the base case for `dp[0][i]` as the count of target character at index 0 in each word of `words`.
4. For each target character from index 1 to index `m-1` (where `m` is the length of the target string), iterate through all words and update the `dp` array. Calculate the number of ways to form the target string using the current word and add it to the previous count stored in `dp`.
5. Add modulo 10^9 + 7 at each step to avoid overflow.
6. The result is the sum of values in the last row of `dp` array, modulo 10^9 + 7.
